================================================================
Web-Interface for Solaris-Servers to display Status-Information
================================================================

The Interface is built on minimalistic HTML5 with jQuery.
If Java-Script is disabled all Status-Information are shown but all eye-candy is hidden.

Tested on Solaris 11 Express, targeted for Open Indiana as well

Installing lighttpd & PHP5:
	sudo pkg install lighttpd
	sudo pkg install

Bundled 'install' Directory:
	 # smf-svc-lighttpd.xml
	  	service-descriptor for solaris SMF
	 	see also:
	 		http://redmine.lighttpd.net/wiki/1/LighttpdOnSolaris
	 		http://blogs.oracle.com/mandy/entry/lighttpd_smf_troubles
	 	
	 # lighttpd.conf
	 	enables SSL on Port 443 and enabled Fast-CGI for PHP5.
	 	see also:
		 	http://redmine.lighttpd.net/wiki/1/Docs:SSL
	
Configuring SolarStatus:
	see conf.php, that's it.
	
Feedback appreciated: kai@meder.info

